Installing Pokecalc
===================

# Prerequisites
* ncurses headers

# Install stack.

Go to haskellstack.org and follow the directions onsite.

# Install purescript.

Run `stack unpack purescript`. Navigate to the purescript directory and run `stack install`.

# Install npm.

Then install some npm packages: bower, pulp, react, react-dom.

# Symlink nodejs to node.

If your version of node is too old, then you can update it by install `n`, the node package manager, and using it to install the latest version of node.

# Install bower.

Run `bower install`.

# Build using pulp.

Run `pulp build` and `pulp browserify --to output.js`.

# Serve!

Python's SimpleHTTPServer can be used to host via `python -m SimpleHTTPServer`.
